    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early form of Spanish that was spoken on the Iberian Peninsula from the 10th century until early 15th century; modern Spanish differs in having had a consonantal readjustment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
